{ A typical motif in this variation, the bishop on d4 is placed perfectly as we support both the c5 and e5-pawn.  9...Nfxd4  doesn't work for Black, because  10.cxd4  Nxd4  runs into  11.Qa4+  winning a piece.   Black can try to castle and unpin the knight to put extra pressure on the e5-pawns however, after  9...Be7  10.Bb5  O-O  11.Bxc6  we trade the knight to eliminate the attacker of the e5-pawn. White is a clean pawn-up. Study more about this variation here. }
