[Black "Model Game: Yu-Labib 2013"]
[Result "*"]

{ This game was played between GM Yangyi Yu  (2668)  and IM Ibrahim Hasan Labib  (2411)  in Antalya, Turkey, in 2013. }
1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. dxc5 Bg4 6. c3 e6 7. Be3 Bxf3 8. Qxf3
Nge7 9. Bb5 { We covered everything in the course till here. } 9... Qc7 10. Bd4
{ This typical idea to defend the c5 and e5-pawns with the bishop we also saw here and here. It is risky for Black to capture the e5-pawn.  10.O-O  would have been a good alternative after  10...Qxe5  11.Nd2  Black is slow with development, and White has a significant advantage. After  11...Nf5  , we have the idea to go  12.Rae1  to open up the f-file after  12...Nxe3  13.fxe3  . After  13...f5  14.b4  Qxc3  15.Nb3  we are threatening Nd4 with a significant advantage. }
10... g5
{ This move is quite weakening, the plan with  10...Nf5  11.O-O  Be7  12.Nd2  would be better for Black, but after  12...O-O  13.Nb3  we are in time to support the bishop and stay a pawn up! }
11. O-O Bg7 12. Re1
{ A logical move, however, the computer prefers  12.Qe3  gaining a tempo by attacking the g5-pawn. After  12...h6  , it's not problematic that after  13.Nd2  Black can attack with  13...Nf5  since after  14.Qd3  Black doesn't want to capture on d4 anyway. }
12... h5 13. Na3 { A cunning idea going for Nc2 to support the bishop. } 13...
g4 14. Qe2 Nf5 15. Nc2
{ The knight is well-placed here, as it supports advancing the queenside pawn majority with b4. }
15... O-O-O 16. b4 Nce7 17. Bd3 Ng6 18. Bxf5 { Weakening the pawn structure. }
18... exf5 19. Qd3 Qd7 20. e6 fxe6 21. c6
{ A great move! The idea is that after  21...bxc6  22.Qa6+  Kb8  23.b5  White has a crushing attack on the kingside. @@StartFEN@@2kr3r/pp1q2b1/4p1n1/2Pp1p1p/1P1B2p1/2PQ4/P1N2PPP/R3R1K1 w - - 0 21@@EndFEN@@  21.Bxg7  Qxg7  22.Rxe6?  would run a nasty fork with  22...Nf4  . }
21... Qf7 22. cxb7+ { White is dominating the game! } 22... Kd7 23. Qb5+ Ke7
24. Bxg7 Qxg7 25. Nd4 Kf6 26. Nxe6 Qd7 27. b8=Q
{ White finishes the game in style. White dominated the game from the opening on! Yu used the idea with Bd4 defending the pawns, he played the instructive Na3-Nc2 to start the kingside attack. }
