[White "2b) Khenkin-Arkell 4...cxd4 Tactics and Model Games"]
[Black "Excersise 1: Khenkin-Arkell 4...cxd4"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1bqk2r/pp2ppbp/2n3pn/3pP3/5Q2/2N1BN2/PPP2PPP/R3KB1R w KQkq - 0 9"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ How do we punish Black for their poor opening play? } 9. O-O-O
{ Castling with tempo and immediately harrassing the d5-pawn. } 9... e6
{ Black has to defend the d5-pawn, which weakens the dark squares. } 10. g4
{ Shutting down the knight on h6 and also creating the opportunity to play g5 and prevent Black's only break in the position with ...f6.  10.Ne4  is a powerful alternative when after  10...Nf5  11.g4  White also reaches a winning position. }
10... O-O 11. g5 { Preventing the ...f6-break. } 11... Nf5
{ Black is threatening ...Qc7 and would have a fantastic position when they win the e5-pawn. }
12. Ne4
{ A great idea. We want to play Nf6+ to weaken Black's king and block the bishop's diagonal to avoid losing the e5-pawn. Afterward, we can start marching our h-pawn and go for a kingside attack. White is winning. }
