{ We want to place the knight on e5. The variation with  8.dxe5  Qxe5  9.Nge2  is less good here since Black will gain a tempo with ...Nf6 when our g4-pawn is undefended. }
8... e4 9. Ne5
{ Our knight is perfectly placed in the center. Trading it for the bishop would misplace Black's king and break their right to castle, so Black should still move the bishop. }
9... Be6 { Black prevents ...Nxf7! } 10. f3
{ We immediately want to trade Black's e4-pawn and open the position. } 10...
exf3
