[White "4b) Bayonet Attack 4...Bg6 Tactics and Model Games "]
[Black "Model Game: Mamedyarov-Jannatul 2021"]
[Result "*"]

{ This game was played in an online Titled Tuesday tournament between GM Shakhriyar Mamedyarov and WCM Ferdous Jannatul in 2021. }
1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. g4 Bg6 5. e6 fxe6 6. h4
{ So far, we covered the theory here. } 6... Bf7
{ Anticipating the threat of h5, Black already moved the bishop back. This is a poor move as the bishop is stuck on f7. }
7. Nf3 Nf6 { Black should play  7...Nd7  preventing Ne5. } 8. Ne5 Nbd7 9. Nxf7
Kxf7 10. g5 { Kicking the knight from the safe square. } 10... Ne4 11. Bd3
{ 11.Nd2  was stronger! } 11... Kg8
{ 11...e5  would be strongest for Black, aiming to free the dark-squared bishop slowly. After  12.Qf3+  Ke8  13.Bxe4  dxe4  14.Qxe4  exd4  15.Qxd4  White would be a pawn-up, and Black has no compensation. }
12. Qg4 Nd6 13. Qxe6+ Nf7 14. h5
{ Threatening g6 and White is winning. The game finished very quickly. } 14...
Nc5 15. dxc5 Qc8 16. Bf5 { White wants to keep the knight pinned! } 16... Qxe6+
17. Bxe6 g6 18. hxg6 hxg6 19. Bxf7+ Kg7 20. Rxh8 Kxh8 21. Bxg6 e5 22. Nc3 Bxc5
23. Bd2 Rf8 24. Nd1 Kg7 25. Bd3 e4 26. Bf1 Kg6 27. b4 Bb6 28. c3 Kh5 29. a4 a6
