[SetUp "1"]

{ How can we hold on to the c5-pawn in an energetic way? } 8. Nb5
{ It looks counterintuitive that we allow Black to trade off the bad French bishop. The point is that we want to prevent Black from play ...Bxc5 and after  8...Bxb5  9.Bxb5+  Nc6  we have accomplished that. We would already be winning after @@StartFEN@@rn2kbnr/ppqb1ppp/4p3/1NPpP3/6P1/4B3/PPP2P1P/R2QKBNR b KQkq - 1 1@@EndFEN@@  8...Qxe5  9.Nf3  when we chase away the queen, and Black can't avoid the fork with Nc7+. }
