{ The third most popular move in the position. We immediately shut down the dark-squared bishop. }
5... fxe6 6. h4 h6
{ This is the most popular move at the Club Player level, Black creates an escape square for the bishop on h7. It's a big mistake, as it weakens the light squares around the king. When Black allows us to kick the bishop with h5, we will always play that. The main move  6...h5  had the same problem but at least after  7.Bd3  Bxd3  Black had the chance to play  7...hxg4  and also ruined our pawn structure. We have already seen the same ideas from the @@StartFEN@@rn1qkbnr/pp2pppp/2p5/3pPb2/3P2P1/8/PPP2P1P/RNBQKBNR b KQkq g3 0 4@@EndFEN@@  4...Be4  5.f3  Bg6  6.e6  fxe6  7.h4  h6  moveorder. The current version is even better for us as we still have the f3-square available for the knight. }
