14... Kd7 15. Qf5+ Ke8 16. Qg6+
{ And the game finishes in a draw, Black had to find the brilliant @@StartFEN@@rn2kbnr/pp2p1p1/2p5/3p3p/3N1BPP/3Q1P2/PqP5/RN2K2R b KQkq - 1 13@@EndFEN@@  13...Na6  and also figure out why @@StartFEN@@r3kbnr/pp2p1p1/n1p3Q1/3p3p/3N1BPP/5P2/PqP5/RN2K2R b KQkq - 3 14@@EndFEN@@  14...Kd8  didn't work. Of course, I can imagine you may not like this game outcome, and you can study the alternative variation here with @@StartFEN@@rn2kbnr/pp2p1p1/2p5/3pq2p/6PP/3Q1P2/PPP1N3/RNB1K2R w KQkq - 0 12@@EndFEN@@  12.Qg6+  , which keeps the fight going! }
